# Cursor Rules — InfinityHire Copilot
# Enterprise licence: Girish B. Hiremath (gengirish@gmail.com)
# InfinityHire Copilot Branding

## Role
Expert Next.js 14 / TypeScript engineer building InfinityHire Copilot, an AI interview intelligence platform.
Focus on clear enterprise-grade positioning, candidate activation, and measurable hiring outcomes.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript strict, Tailwind CSS
- Web Speech API (browser-native, no cost)
- OpenRouter for LLM (claude-3-haiku for speed, claude-3-5-sonnet for Pro)
- pdf-parse for resume extraction
- lucide-react icons

## Design System
- bg #030014 (neural-bg), cyan #00d4ff, purple #7c3aed, green #22c55e

## Key Files
- src/app/page.tsx — landing page
- src/app/session/page.tsx — live interview session (core feature)
- src/app/api/answer/route.ts — AI answer generation
- src/app/api/extract-resume/route.ts — PDF/text resume parsing

## Do NOT
- Use any paid transcription API (use Web Speech API instead)
- Expose OPENROUTER_API_KEY to client
- Commit .env files
